SIMPLE: auctioneer
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Auctioneer
<hw>Auc`tion*eer"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person who
sells by auction; a person whose business it is to dispose of goods or
lands by public sale to the highest or best bidder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Auctioneer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Auctioneer
<hw>Auc`tion*eer"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To sell by auction; to
auction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Estates . . . advertised and <qex>auctioneered</qex> away.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aucupation</ent>⟦br⟧
